1
00:00:01,384 --> 00:00:06,486
Frieren, you must go to
Aureole and speak with Himmel.

2
00:00:08,667 --> 00:00:14,709
On the very northernmost end of the continent, I arrived
at the place the people of this world call Heaven.

3
00:00:15,829 --> 00:00:20,091
I now know it as Aureole,
the land where souls rest.

4
00:00:21,351 --> 00:00:23,112
Many spirits have
gathered there.

5
00:00:24,212 --> 00:00:26,773
I spoke with friends whom
I once fought alongside.

6
00:00:31,107 --> 00:00:32,027
Forgive me.

7
00:00:32,727 --> 00:00:34,748
You have a long journey ahead.

8
00:00:35,768 --> 00:00:37,709
It took the four
of us ten years.

9
00:00:40,490 --> 00:00:41,030
I see.

10
00:00:41,710 --> 00:00:46,412
So we'll be following the same route you took to
the Demon King's castle on your first journey.

11
00:00:57,315 --> 00:00:57,955
That we will.

12
00:00:59,328 --> 00:01:01,129
Another brief
ten-year adventure.

13
00:01:03,731 --> 00:01:05,151
One one-hundredth, eh?

14
00:01:07,753 --> 00:01:10,635
Frieren, you won't be
staying in the Royal Capital?

15
00:01:11,655 --> 00:01:12,876
I'm going to keep traveling.

16
00:01:13,556 --> 00:01:14,337
All by yourself?

17
00:01:14,697 --> 00:01:15,698
It's easier that way.

18
00:01:16,918 --> 00:01:18,940
You're not going to
take on an apprentice.

19
00:01:19,740 --> 00:01:21,941
A journey is better
with someone to talk to.

20
00:01:22,942 --> 00:01:24,503
I fear it would be
a waste of time.

21
00:01:25,183 --> 00:01:27,565
No matter how much I
teach them, they'll surely die.

22
00:01:30,527 --> 00:01:31,387
How cheery.

23
00:01:32,227 --> 00:01:34,208
That's not how
relationships work.

24
00:01:35,148 --> 00:01:36,708
That's how they work for me.

25
00:01:37,209 --> 00:01:38,649
Just consider our adventure.

26
00:01:39,209 --> 00:01:41,830
It's taken up less than one
one-hundredth of my life.

27
00:01:43,410 --> 00:01:45,290
Sounds like me, I suppose.

28
00:01:47,331 --> 00:01:48,531
It's funny, don't you think?

29
00:01:49,832 --> 00:01:50,332
What is?

30
00:01:51,932 --> 00:01:55,813
How much that one
one-hundredth has changed you.

31
00:02:08,594 --> 00:02:09,755
Goodbye for now.

32
00:02:11,375 --> 00:02:12,596
For now.

33
00:02:14,357 --> 00:02:22,681
In comparison, for me,
our journey's been one half.

34
00:02:24,462 --> 00:02:26,482
I've spent one half
of my life with you.

35
00:02:29,124 --> 00:02:31,685
It's going to be much
more than that from here on.

36
00:02:34,859 --> 00:02:42,221
It's a story of love, a sign of the end, a
journey that goes on forever, it's up to you.

37
00:02:42,362 --> 00:02:51,685
It's a memory of a short journey with a hero who
defeated evil that once cast a shadow on this land.

38
00:03:12,971 --> 00:03:30,168
Reiwa mushou ni hito wo wasure saseru Soko ni ikita kiseki mo sabitsuiteku Soredemo
kimi no kotoba mo negai mo yuuki mo Ima wa tashikani watashi no naka de ikiteru

39
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:37,671
Oh my god!

40
00:04:07,387 --> 00:04:09,188
Take these words to heart, Fern.

41
00:04:09,968 --> 00:04:12,849
Before long, Frieren will
be the one in charge of you.

42
00:04:13,169 --> 00:04:14,990
Listen to her and
be a good girl.

43
00:04:16,291 --> 00:04:17,051
If you don't...

44
00:04:18,391 --> 00:04:19,312
If I don't what?

45
00:04:20,132 --> 00:04:22,273
I'll come back as a
ghost and haunt you.

46
00:04:26,575 --> 00:04:31,537
So just to make certain, you're saying that if I'm
a bad girl, you'll pay me a visit after you're gone?

47
00:04:36,416 --> 00:04:38,698
You've grown into
quite the sly young lady.

48
00:04:39,358 --> 00:04:40,819
Wherever did you pick that up?

49
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:44,041
I take it back.

50
00:04:45,902 --> 00:04:52,027
If you're on your best behavior, then I might be
willing to stop by and say hello every now and again.

51
00:04:57,330 --> 00:04:59,292
We should be arriving
at the village soon.

52
00:04:59,312 --> 00:05:02,734
That was fast.

53
00:05:04,408 --> 00:05:05,808
What's that?

54
00:05:05,828 --> 00:05:07,289
Nothing very important.

55
00:05:26,575 --> 00:05:27,675
Greetings, adventurers.

56
00:05:27,996 --> 00:05:29,016
Heading to the mountain pass?

57
00:05:30,243 --> 00:05:31,484
I wouldn't if I were you.

58
00:05:32,264 --> 00:05:34,585
Several people have
gone missing there recently.

59
00:05:35,546 --> 00:05:36,606
Killed by monsters?

60
00:05:37,287 --> 00:05:39,948
They were taken by ghosts,
according to all of the rumors.

61
00:05:40,629 --> 00:05:42,430
Folks have seen them
with their own eyes.

62
00:05:42,670 --> 00:05:43,850
Could be the undead.

63
00:05:44,391 --> 00:05:46,171
Do you know what
these ghosts look like?

64
00:05:46,872 --> 00:05:48,413
I've been too scared to ask.

65
00:05:48,813 --> 00:05:51,334
But if you're that curious, there
are plenty who could tell you.

66
00:06:02,540 --> 00:06:03,600
Here's what we've learned.

67
00:06:04,741 --> 00:06:08,244
The ghosts take on the form of the
Beholder's dead family member or friend.

68
00:06:08,804 --> 00:06:10,486
They look just
as they did in life.

69
00:06:11,887 --> 00:06:14,729
A couple of witnesses even
claim that the ghosts spoke to them.

70
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:18,672
We can conclude this
isn't the work of the undead.

71
00:06:19,412 --> 00:06:20,653
How are you so sure?

72
00:06:20,673 --> 00:06:26,518
The undead are merely
corpses being controlled by magic.

73
00:06:27,538 --> 00:06:29,760
Things like zombies
and skeletons.

74
00:06:31,872 --> 00:06:34,753
But our specters are reported
to appear as they did in life.

75
00:06:35,693 --> 00:06:37,634
A reanimated corpse
couldn't do that.

76
00:06:38,574 --> 00:06:42,075
All that to say, we're dealing with
another type of monster entirely.

77
00:06:44,256 --> 00:06:46,137
Seems you know what
monster that might be.

78
00:06:47,717 --> 00:06:48,897
Yes, a nasty one.

79
00:06:49,398 --> 00:06:51,158
We'd best be
careful to avoid it.

80
00:06:55,119 --> 00:06:56,780
We'll take our leave
first thing in the morning.

81
00:06:57,859 --> 00:07:01,684
But Mistress Frieren, it's clear
the villagers need our help.

82
00:07:02,525 --> 00:07:04,868
You're starting to sound just
like Himmel and the others.

83
00:07:05,449 --> 00:07:08,653
The biggest difference between
you and me is that I am a good girl.

84
00:07:09,434 --> 00:07:09,955
All right.

85
00:07:11,117 --> 00:07:12,679
If you want to
help them, we shall.

86
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:15,903
We'll be traveling through
the mountain pass either way.

87
00:07:31,629 --> 00:07:34,271
The missing villagers
didn't vanish into thin air.

88
00:07:36,112 --> 00:07:37,193
Plenty of clues.

89
00:07:38,914 --> 00:07:39,994
A generous monster.

90
00:07:41,275 --> 00:07:43,697
There are signs of
magic usage all around us.

91
00:07:44,557 --> 00:07:45,218
Yes, indeed.

92
00:07:45,818 --> 00:07:47,099
Can you tell what type it was?

93
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,481
Illusion magic.

94
00:07:50,861 --> 00:07:54,084
In my book on magical
ecology, there's this creature.

95
00:07:55,024 --> 00:07:57,666
It uses lifelike illusions
to lure in its prey.

96
00:07:58,526 --> 00:07:59,407
The Einzahm.

97
00:08:01,315 --> 00:08:07,343
It preys exclusively upon people, using craftiness
rather than strength to lure in its unsuspecting meals.

98
00:08:08,825 --> 00:08:11,128
It tricks its victims with
phantoms of the dead.

99
00:08:12,489 --> 00:08:13,951
And they really fall for that?

100
00:08:15,233 --> 00:08:17,716
Who wouldn't want a final
moment with their dearly departed?

101
00:08:21,472 --> 00:08:26,653
Thankfully for the two of us, the Einzahms' illusions aren't
a threat to mages who know to look beyond their tricks.

102
00:08:27,654 --> 00:08:29,974
They're easily dispersed
by high-density mana.

103
00:08:30,615 --> 00:08:32,295
Basic offensive magic should do.

104
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,836
So all I have to do is
shoot through the phantoms.

105
00:08:38,657 --> 00:08:39,077
Could you?

106
00:08:40,838 --> 00:08:41,718
Yes, of course.

107
00:08:42,758 --> 00:08:44,619
Especially now that
I know they're fake.

108
00:08:45,679 --> 00:08:48,980
I once had to shoot an illusion
of my master begging for her life.

109
00:08:50,813 --> 00:08:54,014
Though to be fair, her begging
not to die was a regular occurrence.

110
00:08:54,694 --> 00:08:57,035
So I can't say that I
felt particularly guilty.

111
00:08:58,056 --> 00:09:01,697
Regardless, it
certainly isn't fun.

112
00:09:01,717 --> 00:09:04,418
Why were you accustomed
to hearing her beg for her life?

113
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,261
The mist is growing thicker.

114
00:09:13,681 --> 00:09:14,481
We're not far.

115
00:09:16,682 --> 00:09:18,883
If you see a specter,
don't hesitate to shoot.

116
00:09:24,693 --> 00:09:25,793
Fern.

117
00:09:30,975 --> 00:09:31,715
There it is.

118
00:09:32,275 --> 00:09:33,535
A phantom of the dead.

119
00:09:36,356 --> 00:09:37,056
No problem.

120
00:09:38,417 --> 00:09:39,037
Just shoot.

121
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:43,158
Look at that, mage.

122
00:09:43,218 --> 00:09:45,639
You've surpassed my
wildest dreams, my dear.

123
00:09:47,759 --> 00:09:49,800
I decided to come
back and say hello.

124
00:09:49,820 --> 00:09:53,381
A girl as good as you are
deserves a friendly haunting.

125
00:09:57,394 --> 00:09:57,915
It knows.

126
00:09:57,955 --> 00:10:01,237
The path of the mage called
and you wisely followed.

127
00:10:01,878 --> 00:10:05,982
Since you were a child, your love
for magic... My cherished memories.

128
00:10:06,102 --> 00:10:08,344
It knows all of them.

129
00:10:08,484 --> 00:10:10,606
And it's using them against me.

130
00:10:11,747 --> 00:10:12,868
How cruel.

131
00:10:15,350 --> 00:10:15,950
Need help?

132
00:10:20,334 --> 00:10:21,135
Seems you might.

133
00:10:29,268 --> 00:10:30,869
I didn't expect to see Himmel.

134
00:10:31,690 --> 00:10:35,033
I was sure it would show me my
master like the last one I defeated did.

135
00:10:37,074 --> 00:10:40,096
Perhaps this means I've changed
since I last encountered one.

136
00:10:44,039 --> 00:10:46,681
Frieren, shoot.

137
00:10:48,002 --> 00:10:48,803
Impressive.

138
00:10:49,804 --> 00:10:51,045
That's just what he'd say.

139
00:11:13,646 --> 00:11:15,928
And now the mountain
pass is safe once more.

140
00:11:17,369 --> 00:11:21,834
That thing I just saw... That was
only a phantom of Master Heiter.

141
00:11:22,814 --> 00:11:23,375
A shadow.

142
00:11:24,456 --> 00:11:24,876
Correct.

143
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:31,102
It's high time we
go see the real thing.

144
00:11:32,523 --> 00:11:35,246
If there's anywhere we might
find him, it would be Aureole.

145
00:11:38,128 --> 00:11:38,669
You're right.

146
00:11:50,182 --> 00:11:50,963
That's a dragon?!

147
00:11:52,484 --> 00:11:54,165
I've never seen
one in real life.

148
00:11:55,866 --> 00:11:56,846
Look at its nest.

149
00:11:58,848 --> 00:11:59,928
Do you see that grimoire?

150
00:12:01,269 --> 00:12:03,191
I've been after that
one for a long time.

151
00:12:04,051 --> 00:12:05,252
That doesn't surprise me.

152
00:12:05,272 --> 00:12:07,954
Why is it there of all places?

153
00:12:08,934 --> 00:12:12,877
Dragons are known to seek out objects
infused with magic to build their nests.

154
00:12:14,288 --> 00:12:15,509
That's a solar dragon.

155
00:12:16,369 --> 00:12:18,890
No doubt it has dined
on many an adventurer.

156
00:12:19,610 --> 00:12:22,291
Grimoire or otherwise, we
should eliminate the beast.

157
00:12:24,232 --> 00:12:25,933
Be careful not to
destroy the nest.

158
00:12:26,473 --> 00:12:26,713
Right.

159
00:12:41,102 --> 00:12:43,783
So, uh, that didn't do anything.

160
00:12:44,143 --> 00:12:46,244
They are very
resilient creatures.

161
00:12:46,684 --> 00:12:47,365
No choice, then.

162
00:12:48,165 --> 00:12:48,445
Run!

163
00:13:07,592 --> 00:13:08,653
Finally lost it.

164
00:13:09,669 --> 00:13:11,130
This one's a fast flyer.

165
00:13:12,151 --> 00:13:13,613
No aerial battle for us.

166
00:13:14,513 --> 00:13:14,934
I thought...

167
00:13:16,055 --> 00:13:17,796
I thought I was
gonna die right there.

168
00:13:18,697 --> 00:13:19,898
Let's head back that way.

169
00:13:20,659 --> 00:13:23,561
If we continue to wear it down,
the brute will eventually give in.

170
00:13:28,526 --> 00:13:29,166
Good point.

171
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:33,870
Playing tag with dragons is not
within a mage's job description.

172
00:13:35,432 --> 00:13:35,692
Uh...

173
00:13:38,758 --> 00:13:40,839
We'll have to take on
another companion.

174
00:13:44,602 --> 00:13:45,382
A frontliner?

175
00:13:45,802 --> 00:13:46,223
Yes.

176
00:13:46,803 --> 00:13:48,644
You're searching
for one, aren't you?

177
00:13:49,925 --> 00:13:53,867
In a village near Regal Canyon,
you'll find a warrior named Stark.

178
00:13:54,468 --> 00:13:56,769
Pick him up on your way
into the Northern Lands.

179
00:13:58,110 --> 00:13:59,191
He's my apprentice.

180
00:14:00,451 --> 00:14:00,932
Right.

181
00:14:02,232 --> 00:14:03,113
Is he any good?

182
00:14:13,677 --> 00:14:16,980
Hard to think there's
a dragon here.

183
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:18,361
It's so peaceful.

184
00:14:18,381 --> 00:14:19,802
'Tis indeed.

185
00:14:22,724 --> 00:14:27,168
I've been meaning to ask, what sort of
spell does that grimoire contain anyway?

186
00:14:28,649 --> 00:14:30,310
One that lets you
see through clothes.

187
00:14:33,853 --> 00:14:37,556
You really do gather only the
strangest of spells, Mistress Frieren.

188
00:14:38,096 --> 00:14:39,237
That is my hobby.

189
00:14:40,572 --> 00:14:42,153
But this one is practical, too.

190
00:14:43,074 --> 00:14:46,464
Depending on what the user views as clothing,
it could reveal hidden weaponry or...

191
00:14:46,488 --> 00:14:49,878
Travelers, may I have
a moment of your time?

192
00:14:51,579 --> 00:14:53,981
Mr. Stark would like
to meet the two of you.

193
00:14:55,222 --> 00:14:56,963
That saves us a
fair bit of trouble.

194
00:15:01,566 --> 00:15:03,047
It was three years back now.

195
00:15:04,128 --> 00:15:07,290
The dragon attacked,
nearly destroying the village.

196
00:15:15,087 --> 00:15:16,268
That's when he appeared.

197
00:15:17,029 --> 00:15:18,511
The brave Mr. Stark.

198
00:15:19,812 --> 00:15:22,715
The dragon was fierce, but
our brave hero didn't break.

199
00:15:23,196 --> 00:15:25,518
After a long standoff,
the monster flew away.

200
00:15:26,279 --> 00:15:27,520
It was a sight to behold.

201
00:15:28,281 --> 00:15:35,388
Since that day, he has lived alongside us in the village, and
that dragon has been too scared to rear its ugly head ever again.

202
00:15:35,689 --> 00:15:37,530
Three whole years of peace.

203
00:15:39,587 --> 00:15:40,367
Perfect.

204
00:15:40,547 --> 00:15:42,308
He sounds like just
the person we need.

205
00:15:42,328 --> 00:15:43,949
The dragon's done for.

206
00:15:43,969 --> 00:15:46,030
I hope you're right.

207
00:15:48,711 --> 00:15:51,532
Do you think I can be a
strong warrior like you?

208
00:15:52,332 --> 00:15:52,932
Sure you can.

209
00:15:53,973 --> 00:15:55,874
But being a warrior's
rougher than it looks.

210
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:02,536
It's Grandma!

211
00:16:08,894 --> 00:16:11,256
So you're the ones who've
been messing with the dragon.

212
00:16:12,217 --> 00:16:13,798
Don't get that
thing too worked up.

213
00:16:14,279 --> 00:16:15,700
You'll put the whole
village in danger.

214
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:17,641
Dragons are serious.

215
00:16:18,122 --> 00:16:20,243
They're not the fairy tale
creatures you think they are.

216
00:16:22,665 --> 00:16:24,047
One of them gave me this scar.

217
00:16:24,487 --> 00:16:28,010
I was fighting a shadow dragon and-
That's child's play as far as injuries go.

218
00:16:30,232 --> 00:16:32,173
My master put you
up to this, didn't he?

219
00:16:32,954 --> 00:16:33,714
Who are you?

220
00:16:35,016 --> 00:16:36,697
I am known as Frieren the Mage.

221
00:16:39,850 --> 00:16:41,871
Hey, Gran, mind
giving us some privacy?

222
00:16:43,613 --> 00:16:44,173
It's alright.

223
00:16:44,854 --> 00:16:46,335
They're acquaintances
of my master.

224
00:16:52,419 --> 00:16:53,179
Don't hold back.

225
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:54,921
He must be furious.

226
00:16:55,641 --> 00:16:57,162
I left without so
much as a word.

227
00:16:58,423 --> 00:17:01,766
Stark, you have no reason
to remain in this village.

228
00:17:02,526 --> 00:17:04,027
Why haven't you
defeated the dragon?

229
00:17:05,268 --> 00:17:07,730
Tell me what you want and
maybe I'll think about sharing.

230
00:17:08,765 --> 00:17:11,606
If you're here to send me back to
my master, you can forget about it.

231
00:17:13,006 --> 00:17:15,766
We're in need of a warrior
and would like for you to join us.

232
00:17:16,426 --> 00:17:19,767
Though before that, we would appreciate
your help in defeating the dragon.

233
00:17:20,847 --> 00:17:22,588
I want the Grimoire in its nest.

234
00:17:23,528 --> 00:17:24,128
Why's that?

235
00:17:24,868 --> 00:17:25,548
It's a hobby.

236
00:17:26,328 --> 00:17:27,589
No particular reason.

237
00:17:28,249 --> 00:17:30,069
We're dealing
with a solar dragon.

238
00:17:30,749 --> 00:17:32,710
You don't fight it
without a good reason.

239
00:17:41,722 --> 00:17:43,683
That's amazing!

240
00:17:43,963 --> 00:17:44,523
You're right.

241
00:17:46,364 --> 00:17:49,486
Mine is that a fool once praised
me for the spells I collected.

242
00:17:50,746 --> 00:17:52,147
Is that enough of a reason?

243
00:17:53,668 --> 00:17:54,748
For a little praise?

244
00:17:58,970 --> 00:17:59,890
That's ridiculous.

245
00:18:00,271 --> 00:18:00,651
Agreed.

246
00:18:02,832 --> 00:18:04,293
I don't mind joining your party.

247
00:18:05,553 --> 00:18:07,554
I can tell my master
put you up to this.

248
00:18:08,555 --> 00:18:09,375
But no matter.

249
00:18:10,010 --> 00:18:12,233
My priority is taking
out the Solar Dragon.

250
00:18:13,054 --> 00:18:14,996
I've had difficulties
defeating it on my own.

251
00:18:16,759 --> 00:18:19,362
For you, it'd be
no issue, right?

252
00:18:20,343 --> 00:18:23,507
No, not at all if you can keep
the beast busy for 30 seconds.

253
00:18:24,809 --> 00:18:25,610
Loud and clear.

254
00:18:26,971 --> 00:18:28,213
Just 30 seconds, huh?

255
00:18:30,775 --> 00:18:32,916
and that really
has to be my job.

256
00:18:33,196 --> 00:18:35,317
Is there some kind of
joke that I'm missing here?

257
00:18:36,118 --> 00:18:37,938
I can't say that
I'm very surprised.

258
00:18:38,899 --> 00:18:42,020
Tell me, Stark, just how many
monsters have you fought?

259
00:18:42,381 --> 00:18:44,041
A big fat zero, okay?

260
00:18:44,201 --> 00:18:46,442
Don't abandon me,
Frieren, I need your help.

261
00:18:47,463 --> 00:18:52,966
I worked up the guts to confront the dragon,
but I was so terrified I couldn't move a muscle.

262
00:18:53,746 --> 00:18:55,047
I mean, come on.

263
00:18:55,487 --> 00:18:57,688
That thing slices through
houses like they're veggies.

264
00:18:59,115 --> 00:19:01,864
The human being doesn't
stand a chance against it!

265
00:19:02,527 --> 00:19:04,995
I figured that it spared me on a whim, but…

266
00:19:09,093 --> 00:19:12,695
The dragon stopped attacking the village
after that and I was treated like a hero!

267
00:19:13,535 --> 00:19:15,956
The villagers are too
nice for their own good!

268
00:19:16,596 --> 00:19:18,657
A strong young man
like you should eat up!

269
00:19:18,697 --> 00:19:19,097
Stark!

270
00:19:19,377 --> 00:19:22,059
After supper, you gotta
show me all your latest moves!

271
00:19:22,519 --> 00:19:26,080
There's no way I could leave
this place even if I wanted to!

272
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,421
This one's no good.

273
00:19:27,701 --> 00:19:30,382
We should get going
and find someone serious.

274
00:19:30,462 --> 00:19:32,163
Please don't leave
me here to rot!

275
00:19:33,695 --> 00:19:35,957
No, he can hold off the dragon.

276
00:19:36,778 --> 00:19:37,738
I'm certain of it.

277
00:19:38,559 --> 00:19:41,201
Fine, but it'll take more
than a pat on the back.

278
00:20:02,401 --> 00:20:05,143
Well, Stark, you have
till tomorrow morning.

279
00:20:06,784 --> 00:20:07,604
Think it all through.

280
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:11,547
You know as well as I do
you can't keep the hero act up.

281
00:20:26,056 --> 00:20:27,717
I heard you met Mr. Stark.

282
00:20:28,878 --> 00:20:30,319
A fine young man, isn't he?

283
00:20:30,723 --> 00:20:31,703
He's just lovely.

284
00:20:31,903 --> 00:20:35,244
When we cook for him, it seems his
stomach is almost as big as his smile.

285
00:20:36,324 --> 00:20:38,265
Everyone really
seems to love that guy.

286
00:20:39,165 --> 00:20:40,105
I'm sure that they do.

287
00:20:40,165 --> 00:20:42,086
He struck me as a
kind sort of person.

288
00:20:43,206 --> 00:20:44,006
Maybe so.

289
00:20:45,487 --> 00:20:47,667
I was distracted by
his immense cowardice.

290
00:20:48,468 --> 00:20:50,148
The lad is a little
yellow-bellied.

291
00:20:51,008 --> 00:20:54,109
But let's think back to your first
time going up against a monster.

292
00:20:56,190 --> 00:20:56,850
Never mind.

293
00:20:56,910 --> 00:20:57,790
Let's think forward.

294
00:21:01,126 --> 00:21:02,206
You were cute once.

295
00:21:02,847 --> 00:21:05,447
Not only are you taller than
me now, but scarier, too.

296
00:21:05,467 --> 00:21:10,889
What I want to know is why
the dragon hasn't been attacking.

297
00:21:11,550 --> 00:21:12,190
Who can say?

298
00:21:12,210 --> 00:21:15,710
It might be bored of
this place, or perhaps...

299
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,867
What was that sound?

300
00:21:20,593 --> 00:21:21,693
Stark, I imagine.

301
00:21:23,974 --> 00:21:25,914
If you're curious, you
should go check on him.

302
00:21:26,595 --> 00:21:27,335
I'm going to bed.

303
00:21:45,257 --> 00:21:45,757
Right.

304
00:21:46,758 --> 00:21:47,658
Is he any good?

305
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:55,083
When his village was attacked by
monsters, he fled and never looked back.

306
00:21:56,323 --> 00:21:58,485
He's a coward who
left his home to burn.

307
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:01,787
He's like me.

308
00:22:04,969 --> 00:22:07,930
That's why I hammered
everything I know into the boy.

309
00:22:09,091 --> 00:22:12,313
Now he's finally ready to fight
for someone other than himself.

310
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:14,870
You've sold me.

311
00:22:15,951 --> 00:22:22,833
He is any good.

312
00:22:38,418 --> 00:22:39,058
I see now.

313
00:22:39,238 --> 00:22:41,199
Your training is what
made this fissure.

